The Biden-Harris Administration is prioritizing the advancement of opportunity, equity, and safety for Asian American, Native Hawaiian, and Pacific Islander (AA and NHPI) communities. They are celebrating the diversity and contributions of these communities while also addressing the discrimination and barriers they face. The administration has taken steps to combat anti-Asian violence and discrimination, including signing the COVID-19 Hate Crimes Act into law. They have also focused on promoting equitable data collection, improving healthcare outcomes, and creating economic opportunities for AA and NHPI communities. The administration has implemented measures to address housing discrimination, ensure educational equity, and provide language access. They are committed to advancing racial equity and supporting underserved communities through various initiatives and partnerships. The administration is also working to reform the immigration system and has prioritized diversity in their own appointments, including AA and NHPI individuals leading critical agencies.